## DBsubject(Algebra)
## DBchapter(Exponential functions)
## DBsection(Introduction to the Family of Exponential Functions)
## Institution(Loyola University Chicago and Fort Lewis College)
## Author(Adam Spiegler and Paul Pearson)
## TitleText1('Functions Modeling Change')
## AuthorText1('Connally')
## EditionText1('3')
## Section1('3.1')
## Problem1('14')
## TitleText2('Functions Modeling Change')
## AuthorText2('Connally')
## EditionText2('4')
## Section2('4.1')
## Problem2('14')
## KEYWORDS('exponential functions','growth rate','growth factor')


####################################
#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Numeric");


####################################
#  Setup

Context("Numeric");

$a = non_zero_random(-400,400,100)+1750;
$b = non_zero_random(-0.3,0.3,0.01)+1.593;
$decimal = $b - 1;
$r = $decimal*100;

$answera = Real("$a");
$answerb = Real("$b");
$answerc = Real("$r");


#####################################
#  Main text

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find the initial value \(a\),
growth/decay factor \(b\), and
growth/decay rate \(r\) for the
following exponential function:
$PAR
\[ Q(t) = $a($b)^t \]
$PAR
(a) The initial value is \(a = \)
\{ ans_rule(10) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$PAR
(b) The growth factor is \(b = \)
\{ ans_rule(10) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$PAR
(c) The growth rate is \(r = \)
\{ ans_rule(10) \} $PERCENT
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$BR
${BITALIC}(Note that if \(r\) gives a decay rate you
should have \(r < 0\).)$EITALIC

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;


#####################################
#  Answer evaluation

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

ANS($answera->cmp() );
ANS($answerb->cmp() );
ANS($answerc->cmp() );


#####################################
#  Solution

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
This is already in  standard form, \( Q=ab^t = $a($b)^t \),
so \( a = $a \), \( b = $b \), and \( r = 1 - b = $decimal \) or $r${PERCENT}.

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

COMMENT('MathObject version');
ENDDOCUMENT();
